-- India L&T Finance's share offer subscribed 3.2 times  
-- By Sumeet Chatterjee
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 11:28AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 11 (Reuters) - A share sale by India's L&T Finance Holdings Ltd <LTFH.NS> to raise at least $34 million on Wednesday saw investors bidding for 3.2 times the number of shares on offer, according to stock exchange data.

L&T Finance, a unit of engineering conglomerate Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS>, saw demand for 87.9 million shares versus the 27.6 million shares it was offering at a base price of 74 rupees apiece, the data showed.